<div class="about-container">
    <h2>About Can I Recycle THAT?</h2>
    
    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Why We Built This</h3>
        <p>
            In 2026, recycling contamination—the technical term for mis-sorted items—remains a major challenge for the waste industry, 
            with average contamination rates in the U.S. hovering around 17% to 25%. This means that roughly one out of every 
            four or five items placed in a blue bin doesn't belong there. The impact is significant: a single greasy 
            pizza box or half-full soda bottle can ruin an entire batch of clean paper, while "tanglers" like plastic 
            bags and garden hoses can jam heavy machinery, leading to facility shutdowns. We built this app to empower individuals with the knowledge they need to recycle correctly, 
            reduce contamination, and ultimately help create a cleaner, more sustainable Utah.
        </p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>How It Works</h3>
        <p>
            Can I Recycle THAT? uses advanced machine learning technology to identify and classify waste items. Simply take a photo of the item you're unsure about, upload it to our app, and instantly receive:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Accurate classification of the waste type</li>
            <li>Detailed disposal instructions specific to Utah</li>
            <li>Environmental impact information</li>
            <li>Confidence level of the classification</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Our Mission</h3>
        <p>
            Our mission is to help residents of Utah make informed decisions about waste disposal and recycling. With unclear guidelines and significant fines for improper recycling, we created this app to take the guesswork out of the process.
        </p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Waste Categories We Recognize</h3>
        <p>Our AI model can identify and provide guidance for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Cardboard</li>
            <li>Food Organics</li>
            <li>Glass</li>
            <li>Metal</li>
            <li>Miscellaneous Trash</li>
            <li>Paper</li>
            <li>Plastic</li>
            <li>Textile Trash</li>
            <li>Vegetation</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Important Note</h3>
        <p>
            While we strive for accuracy, always refer to your local waste management facility's guidelines for the most up-to-date information. Requirements may vary by location within Utah.
        </p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="resources-card">
        <h3>Learn More About Recycling</h3>
        <p>For more information on how to recycle properly in Utah, check out these resources:</p>
        <ul class="resources-list">
            <li><a href="https://www.utah.gov" target="_blank">Utah.gov - Official State Resources</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.epa.gov/recycle" target="_blank">EPA - Recycling Guide</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.earth911.com" target="_blank">Earth911 - Find Recycling Centers Near You</a></li>
            <li>Check your local city or county waste management website for specific guidelines</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    
    <div class="about-footer">
        <p>Built with ♻️ for a cleaner Utah</p>
    </div>
</div>

